Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:02:29,549 --> 00:02:30,910
Let's eat.

3
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:32,456
It looks delicious!

4
00:02:34,895 --> 00:02:36,025
So...

5
00:02:36,025 --> 00:02:37,608
You should join the training.

6
00:02:37,608 --> 00:02:41,499
Of course! You said that it's
starting this afternoon.

7
00:02:42,457 --> 00:02:47,407
I was absolutely going to go, of course.
That's why I'm here. No matter what.

8
00:02:49,305 --> 00:02:51,536
It's probably not your first kiss at age 23.

9
00:03:01,725 --> 00:03:05,925
It was just a smooch for like
middle school sweethearts.

10
00:03:06,123 --> 00:03:07,654
You're panicking.

11
00:03:14,302 --> 00:03:15,742
Who's panicking?

12
00:03:16,050 --> 00:03:19,429
I'm not! Why would I panic over
such a petty thing!

13
00:03:20,196 --> 00:03:23,326
It's like a hello.

14
00:03:23,326 --> 00:03:24,771
It's like that for me too.

15
00:03:26,060 --> 00:03:27,677
It's not for me.

16
00:03:28,787 --> 00:03:30,099
Huh?

17
00:03:32,512 --> 00:03:34,720
I don't do it as hello.

18
00:03:37,741 --> 00:03:40,845
I'm not a easy guy like that.

19
00:03:45,137 --> 00:03:47,001
I am...

20
00:03:47,464 --> 00:03:52,504
I thought that you may feel awkward
if I put too much meaning into that.

21
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,680
It's not awkward, but it's...

22
00:03:56,816 --> 00:04:03,058
It was like a cheer up thing for the future star,
who's just made the hardest choice in her life.

23
00:04:03,397 --> 00:04:05,069
Something like that?

24
00:04:09,782 --> 00:04:13,663
Then we can just enjoy the breakfast
without you laughing all weird like this right?

25
00:04:18,953 --> 00:04:20,361
Ok. Let's eat.

26
00:04:27,897 --> 00:04:31,867
You got $50,000 investment as soon as
your fund was decided.

27
00:04:31,867 --> 00:04:33,664
I think so.

28
00:04:33,664 --> 00:04:36,580
As for project B, you received $170,000
four months after.

29
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:40,327
Additionally you received $30,000 for project A.

30
00:04:40,327 --> 00:04:43,716
I think I took about $200,000.

31
00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:47,315
You've received $320,000 total for
Projects A, B, C, and D.

32
00:04:47,315 --> 00:04:52,747
-Can I get something to drink?
-You've never made a contract for a song right?

33
00:04:53,641 --> 00:04:58,425
I did because the policies sort of changed.

34
00:04:58,425 --> 00:05:01,565
Anyways, we're getting onto it right now.

35
00:05:01,565 --> 00:05:04,533
Where's all the money you've received?

36
00:05:05,737 --> 00:05:08,553
You know there are processing costs.

37
00:05:08,553 --> 00:05:12,043
All the whiskeys and wines that you drink.
Hotels that you go...

38
00:05:14,087 --> 00:05:18,353
You know the world of creation, Representative Yu.

39
00:05:18,353 --> 00:05:20,981
I don't think people like you understand.

40
00:05:20,981 --> 00:05:23,292
I don't need to know.
And I don't want to know.

41
00:05:23,292 --> 00:05:26,353
Provide evidence for your spending by next week.

42
00:05:26,353 --> 00:05:29,721
You would have to admit to embezzlement
for the ones that you can't prove.

43
00:05:29,721 --> 00:05:32,887
Hey man, you know?

44
00:05:32,887 --> 00:05:37,566
Then you would have to first find out
if I spent all that $320,000.

45
00:05:38,476 --> 00:05:39,945
What do you mean?

46
00:05:41,664 --> 00:05:43,278
Exactly as I said.

47
00:05:44,171 --> 00:05:47,799
You know you weren't the one that
ran this fund in the beginning.

48
00:05:47,799 --> 00:05:52,119
When I got the money,
it was when the other Rep Yu was around.

49
00:05:52,119 --> 00:05:56,081
That guy! Your cousin.
Yu Jae Joon.

50
00:05:57,995 --> 00:06:01,883
Didn't he tell you anything?

51
00:06:12,849 --> 00:06:15,968
Can you hear that? You know those guys are
pretty new themselves.

52
00:06:16,248 --> 00:06:19,304
Someone like you can even call
FF or 20 Body and ...

53
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:24,917
-Let's talk after you see her!
-That's why I'm saying FF or 20 Body...

54
00:06:24,917 --> 00:06:27,394
Can you even afford those guys?

55
00:06:27,394 --> 00:06:31,275
If it's working with Hong Jae Yi,
who would even ask for money?

56
00:06:32,603 --> 00:06:34,798
Stop using your throat but
use your breath instead!

57
00:06:34,798 --> 00:06:36,729
Oh, you're here!

58
00:06:36,993 --> 00:06:39,159
This is Go Eun Bi.
This is Producer Gu Jak.

59
00:06:39,542 --> 00:06:40,542
Say hi.

60
00:06:41,336 --> 00:06:43,938
Ms. Go Eun Bi.
Nice to meet you.

61
00:06:43,938 --> 00:06:48,486
-Nice to meet you.
-Oh yes.

62
00:06:49,142 --> 00:06:53,934
Shouldn't the corporations sponsor
cultural movements?

63
00:06:53,934 --> 00:06:59,574
A big corporation such as this,
giving such a meager amount of money...

64
00:07:00,249 --> 00:07:04,706
then asking what? Investment? Profit?

65
00:07:04,706 --> 00:07:07,507
That's not right.

66
00:07:12,033 --> 00:07:13,468
Is it no-smoking?

67
00:07:19,127 --> 00:07:20,546
Take a look.

68
00:07:22,290 --> 00:07:27,812
This is when the lead actress runs out to the
center of the stage in shock.

69
00:07:27,812 --> 00:07:29,832
It's the theme song.

70
00:07:34,831 --> 00:07:41,461
<i>~It's not. It's not love.
Absolutely not. ~</i>

71
00:07:42,361 --> 00:07:45,996
<i>~Whenever I see you.~</i>

72
00:07:45,996 --> 00:07:48,835
Your heart is being stumbled
by the man whom you thought you couldn't love.

73
00:07:49,627 --> 00:07:53,796
<i>~But my heart. My love. ~</i>

74
00:07:54,096 --> 00:07:57,976
<i>~Whenver I call you it swift wind blows by. ~</i>

75
00:07:57,976 --> 00:08:05,686
<i>~Since when was it? Since it became silver platter. ~</i>

76
00:08:05,686 --> 00:08:09,756
<i>~Since when was it?~</i>

77
00:08:10,105 --> 00:08:15,345
<i>~The excitement that I'm feeling for the first time.~</i>

78
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:22,734
<i>~Even if I try to turn my head
and look away from you.~</i>

79
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:31,401
<i>~Even if I shake my body and shake
off the silver fox fur...~</i>

80
00:08:32,012 --> 00:08:39,853
<i>~I find myself holding you in my arms.~</i>

81
00:08:40,784 --> 00:08:44,343
<i>~Your wound that only I know.~</i>

82
00:08:44,809 --> 00:08:49,536
<i>~Your wound that I hold in my arms.~</i>

83
00:08:57,214 --> 00:09:00,900
I don't think I should sing it like this.

84
00:09:08,139 --> 00:09:10,301
It's beating quite excitedly right?

85
00:09:13,136 --> 00:09:15,827
You like the song?

86
00:09:20,901 --> 00:09:23,788
Is there someone that can impress
Hong Jae Yi in Korea?

87
00:09:28,112 --> 00:09:29,549
Hello!

88
00:09:29,549 --> 00:09:31,281
Do you know me?

89
00:09:34,004 --> 00:09:40,816
Your songs, I mean your work.
I know all of them.

90
00:09:42,107 --> 00:09:45,950
Thank you. Now will you excuse us?

91
00:09:45,950 --> 00:09:48,817
I have something to discuss with him.

92
00:09:48,817 --> 00:09:50,769
The door was open.

93
00:09:53,570 --> 00:09:55,561
We're doing lessons right now.

94
00:09:55,561 --> 00:10:02,462
That's ok. I'll just leave.
You guys have your conversation.

95
00:10:15,929 --> 00:10:18,803
You shouldn't play around with kids.

96
00:10:18,803 --> 00:10:23,145
If you say that you're not just playing around,
with someone like that then it's insulting me.

97
00:10:25,284 --> 00:10:27,622
Say what you want and leave.

98
00:10:37,450 --> 00:10:39,237
Just take a seat!

99
00:10:39,237 --> 00:10:42,974
If we want to cover it,
we can cover the whole thing.

100
00:10:42,974 --> 00:10:46,654
You know funds with that big of a size,
taking some money out for mutual benefits is...

101
00:10:47,016 --> 00:10:51,639
Isn't it Father? When can there be a
deal without a broker's fee?

102
00:10:51,639 --> 00:10:55,580
I said that it's not important whether you
took the money or you didn't.

103
00:10:55,580 --> 00:11:00,548
The important part is whether it will be known
that you took the money or you didn't.

104
00:10:59,850 --> 00:11:01,710
That's what's...

105
00:11:03,950 --> 00:11:06,610
Since when were you here?
You didn't even let us know.

106
00:11:06,610 --> 00:11:08,580
You were talking.

107
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:12,280
- Who taught you manners...
-Sit.

108
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:25,350
I heard that you were taking care of the fund
Jae Joon used to work on.

109
00:11:25,350 --> 00:11:28,380
Yes, they all expired.

110
00:11:28,380 --> 00:11:34,210
I think Jae Joon made some mistakes
during the beginning of the fund.

111
00:11:34,210 --> 00:11:36,250
Father those weren't mistakes.

112
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:38,610
Yes, they weren't mistakes.

113
00:11:38,610 --> 00:11:43,228
If you call investing 3 to 4 times for a company
that has no intention of performing,

114
00:11:43,228 --> 00:11:46,569
You should say that him doing business
at all is a mistake.

115
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,810
Hey!

116
00:11:48,810 --> 00:11:51,980
It was a mistake. Jae Joon's mistake.

117
00:11:51,980 --> 00:11:54,050
Father,

118
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:05,010
We let you run the fund believing
that you may put it back on course.

119
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:09,050
So, if you just blame Jae Joon for his mistakes,

120
00:12:09,050 --> 00:12:13,950
you're just as incapable as he is.

121
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:17,210
Uncle.

122
00:12:17,210 --> 00:12:21,310
In baseball, if the pitcher makes the bases loaded,

123
00:12:21,310 --> 00:12:23,410
and leaves the game to the substitute pitcher,
the stats will be recorded...

124
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:29,550
Yes, on the first pitcher.
He will have the runs in his stats.

125
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:32,950
However, the pitcher that gets in the game
when the bases are loaded.

126
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:39,510
Takes a hit and losing the game is something
anyone can do.

127
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:42,380
What kind of a pitcher are you?

128
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:45,580
Are you the one that gets three strikes?

129
00:12:45,580 --> 00:12:48,480
Saving the team and the face of the first pitcher?

130
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,210
You take the win.

131
00:12:50,210 --> 00:12:52,610
Show everyone your ability.

132
00:12:52,610 --> 00:12:57,010
Isn't that the way to build your career?

133
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:07,650
So, you're coming back to musicals with that song?

134
00:13:09,210 --> 00:13:11,580
Umm... yeah.

135
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:19,150
If you don't like Rep Yu,
you can just do it with me alone.

136
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:22,050
As long as you say you're coming back.

137
00:13:22,650 --> 00:13:27,550
Do you know what it means that you and I
are starting the musical again?

138
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:29,780
You already know clearly.

139
00:13:29,780 --> 00:13:36,480
Yes. It's because I'm fully aware of what it means.

140
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:49,950
To Hong Jae Yi, musical is Bae Kang Hee.

141
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:55,280
Bae Kang Hee is musical.

142
00:13:57,450 --> 00:14:01,150
That's what I'm trying to get rid of.

143
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:03,780
Help me.

144
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:06,950
Help you with what?

145
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:09,110
Help you try to get away from me?

146
00:14:09,110 --> 00:14:12,180
You're the one who left me.

147
00:14:13,010 --> 00:14:16,610
At that time...you know that
that was the only choice for me.

148
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:19,450
You admitted so yourself.

149
00:14:20,410 --> 00:14:22,910
Because you loved yourself so much,

150
00:14:22,910 --> 00:14:26,410
You chose to marry your husband.

151
00:14:28,010 --> 00:14:30,650
There's no man.

152
00:14:30,650 --> 00:14:34,410
No man that can have all of Bae Kang Hee.

153
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:37,980
But...

154
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:41,550
I can give you the big part.

155
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:46,710
No.

156
00:14:47,180 --> 00:14:49,580
I left because I hate complicated things.
And now...

157
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:51,080
So?

158
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:54,050
Has it become simple?

159
00:14:54,550 --> 00:14:56,710
Not yet.

160
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:58,950
Because of that girl earlier?

161
00:15:00,050 --> 00:15:02,080
Maybe...

162
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:07,010
I don't know.
I wonder if it can be that simple.

163
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:18,880
I just hate irresponsible people
who care about nothing but themselves.

164
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:24,010
There are plenty of those people.

165
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:26,980
Especially in the field we're working on.

166
00:15:28,050 --> 00:15:30,280
Talent.

167
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:35,050
If they can't use it for others,
for the world,

168
00:15:35,050 --> 00:15:37,280
Then it's just useless.

169
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:40,814
That's why people like you should help them so that
they can use their talent

170
00:15:40,814 --> 00:15:44,803
By investing money and giving them opportunities.

171
00:15:46,610 --> 00:15:50,210
Have you gotten a call from someone?

172
00:15:50,810 --> 00:15:53,380
I always get calls.

173
00:15:54,310 --> 00:15:58,110
-President Han.
-Representative Yu.

174
00:15:58,550 --> 00:16:03,680
Because of selfish people who only love
themselves, and who only do what they want to do,

175
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:07,380
Because of people who act and sing even
though they are starving,

176
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:10,750
We're here today.

177
00:16:11,850 --> 00:16:15,610
In the process, injustice could happen.

178
00:16:15,610 --> 00:16:18,550
There are situations that we can never understand.

179
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:21,710
Once the curtains unveil and the audience applauds,

180
00:16:21,710 --> 00:16:23,710
you tend to forget everything.

181
00:16:23,710 --> 00:16:26,450
Everything gets covered.

182
00:16:26,450 --> 00:16:32,410
What do you want me to do?

183
00:16:32,850 --> 00:16:35,510
You don't have to do something for me.

184
00:16:35,510 --> 00:16:39,480
I'm just saying that you don't
have to be so tough on everyone.

185
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:21,680
That was sick! Did you see that?

186
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,880
When the lead actress came up after about 42 minutes.

187
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,610
I'm not a bad person. Don't hit me.

188
00:17:26,610 --> 00:17:30,110
I just wanted to earn my way.
We're all the same people.

189
00:17:30,110 --> 00:17:32,250
Did you memorize it by watching it just once?

190
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:33,110
That's so cool.

191
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:37,280
For people like me, it gets straight into
my head after just watching it once.

192
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:38,910
It's not something anyone can do.

193
00:17:38,910 --> 00:17:39,980
What's interesting is that...

194
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:43,250
The scene right after. The poem.

195
00:17:43,250 --> 00:17:45,350
The poem was from the roof scene.

196
00:17:45,350 --> 00:17:49,110
What are you talking about? Do you know
how many times I've watched this?

197
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:50,910
You said it was your first time!

198
00:17:50,910 --> 00:17:54,280
You said that you memorized
it after watching it once.

199
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:58,710
That's not what's important here.

200
00:17:58,710 --> 00:18:04,680
The point here is that, the next scene is
the mountain scene.

201
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:07,310
It's not.

202
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:11,350
You wanna bet?

203
00:18:11,350 --> 00:18:13,980
The loser gets to take everyone out
tonight for a full course dinner.

204
00:18:13,980 --> 00:18:15,950
Call.

205
00:18:15,950 --> 00:18:20,280
You've invested on a company
that performed once in 1991.

206
00:18:20,281 --> 00:18:24,610
Now you're saying that
you've invested in their potential?

207
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:27,710
Director Lee, who has produced
"The Man of the King,"

208
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:31,556
is a man who has never produced in 15 years.

209
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:35,180
For artists, miracles seldom occur.

210
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:37,380
Representative Yu!

211
00:18:37,380 --> 00:18:40,150
They say that you're the venomous snake
in the field.

212
00:18:40,150 --> 00:18:42,650
You know better than anyone that Yu Jae Joon
is not the man who would invest knowing these.

213
00:18:42,650 --> 00:18:45,710
How dare you to play dumb?

214
00:18:45,710 --> 00:18:49,110
You always talk about honest,
public entrepreneurship.

215
00:18:49,110 --> 00:18:53,110
It's always the same family business,
dirty crap kept within family.

216
00:18:53,110 --> 00:18:56,050
It's negative 37% on the 50 million fund.

217
00:18:56,050 --> 00:18:58,080
That's 20 million dollars.

218
00:18:58,080 --> 00:19:00,610
Didn't you guys take all of these?

219
00:19:00,610 --> 00:19:07,661
The agreement that we will minimize the loss on
Dae Hak Ro fund is still in effect.

220
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:13,453
I hope everyone understands that we had put in
our utmost attention to Amour Fund.

221
00:19:13,453 --> 00:19:15,650
Hold on.
Let's just hear this out.

222
00:19:15,650 --> 00:19:17,150
Amour Fund is still going well.

223
00:19:17,150 --> 00:19:18,850
But still.

224
00:19:18,850 --> 00:19:22,864
How can the 10 million dollar budget for Amour Fund
cover the loss of 50 million dollars?

225
00:19:22,864 --> 00:19:24,880
Do you know what the profit should be then?

226
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:27,150
300%

227
00:19:27,150 --> 00:19:31,380
Are you confident that you can make 300% profit?

228
00:19:39,350 --> 00:19:41,280
Let's start all over tomorrow.

229
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:43,550
What time can you come?

230
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:46,680
We already decided to practice together.

231
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:50,550
I feel that practicing in the office is best.

232
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:02,950
Guests come to your house and stuff...

233
00:20:08,650 --> 00:20:11,410
Kang Hee...

234
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:13,350
Used to be a very special person to me.

235
00:20:13,350 --> 00:20:17,680
I understand very well.

236
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:21,380
Bae Kang Hee, even to me,
is a stunning person.

237
00:20:21,380 --> 00:20:22,950
She really is cool.

238
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:24,350
Hey.

239
00:20:24,350 --> 00:20:26,450
You should listen!

240
00:20:26,450 --> 00:20:29,250
She USED TO BE a special person.

241
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:31,380
USED TO BE.

242
00:20:35,780 --> 00:20:38,750
That's not the only reason.

243
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:40,710
Bok Ja too.

244
00:20:40,710 --> 00:20:46,550
Anyways, I think it's best that I practice in
the office, teacher.

245
00:20:46,550 --> 00:20:49,210
-Eun Bi!
-Teacher!

246
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,680
Like you said.

247
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:55,110
I made the hardest decision in my life.

