508
00:42:35,650 --> 00:42:40,980
<i>~The only thing that I want is!~</i>

509
00:42:40,980 --> 00:42:45,350
<i>~But I can't stop.~</i>

510
00:42:45,350 --> 00:42:49,580
<i>~My love...~</i>

511
00:42:49,580 --> 00:42:54,280
<i>~I'll be honest with all of my feelings today.~</i>

512
00:42:54,280 --> 00:43:01,050
<i>~I will say it with my one last breath.~</i>

513
00:43:01,050 --> 00:43:07,380
<i>~You're my only love.~</i>

514
00:43:08,380 --> 00:43:09,580
Enough.

515
00:43:09,580 --> 00:43:11,280
That's good enough.

516
00:43:12,550 --> 00:43:16,150
The song is really good. The singing is...

517
00:43:16,150 --> 00:43:19,210
I can't bear it.

518
00:43:19,210 --> 00:43:20,910
I'm sorry.

519
00:43:20,910 --> 00:43:24,450
It's ok. We're not auditioning for actress here.

520
00:43:24,450 --> 00:43:28,450
Is it that the company is that poor to have
an actress who's not ready to come up?

521
00:43:28,450 --> 00:43:31,375
Or were you taking this lightly?

522
00:43:32,250 --> 00:43:35,110
It's not like that.

523
00:43:35,110 --> 00:43:38,550
The key was set for her.

524
00:43:38,550 --> 00:43:45,010
So if you get sponsored here,
will you have her as the lead actress?

525
00:43:46,610 --> 00:43:48,550
We only need to talk about the piece here.

526
00:43:48,550 --> 00:43:50,550
- First...
- Musical pieces...

527
00:43:50,550 --> 00:43:55,050
are things that need lots of hands
in order to have their lives prolonged.

528
00:43:55,050 --> 00:44:01,010
We can't be sponsoring on a song like this,
that's been written to suit one person.

529
00:44:01,010 --> 00:44:04,750
No matter how good the piece is,
if it's like this...

530
00:44:04,750 --> 00:44:07,650
Wouldn't there be problems with sponsoring?

531
00:44:08,410 --> 00:44:10,550
It's not that.

532
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:15,097
Yes it's me.
I was the one who lowered the keys.

533
00:44:15,097 --> 00:44:18,255
Other actresses can sing it with high tones.

534
00:44:18,255 --> 00:44:23,680
It's not high.
It's normal.

535
00:44:23,850 --> 00:44:29,280
Yes. It's normal.

536
00:44:30,580 --> 00:44:32,950
I can't take it anymore.

537
00:44:33,080 --> 00:44:37,930
Seriously. You don't even have the basics.
How dare you to...

538
00:44:37,930 --> 00:44:41,009
If you don't have talent, you should give up.

539
00:44:41,009 --> 00:44:44,680
Aren't you ashamed?

540
00:44:46,610 --> 00:44:49,910
I'm sorry.

541
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:55,010
You've given me the opportunity.
I'm not ashamed.

542
00:44:55,180 --> 00:44:57,450
-I am sorry.
-It's fine.

543
00:44:57,450 --> 00:45:02,050
The professionals hate the word "sorry."

544
00:45:02,210 --> 00:45:05,910
Be responsible and quit.

545
00:45:06,050 --> 00:45:13,150
Having not enough talent is enough.
Don't ask for forgiveness. I hate such rudeness.

546
00:45:13,280 --> 00:45:16,110
Kang Hee!

547
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:19,710
Let's take a 10 minute break.

548
00:45:28,510 --> 00:45:34,450
Kang Hee.

549
00:45:41,580 --> 00:45:43,510
Is something wrong?

550
00:45:43,650 --> 00:45:45,965
I want to see Bae Kang Hee for a sec.

551
00:45:48,550 --> 00:45:49,980
What she said as a judge...

552
00:45:50,150 --> 00:45:53,696
It's not because of that.

553
00:45:55,980 --> 00:45:57,750
I...

554
00:45:57,910 --> 00:46:02,350
I wanted to get her autograph.

555
00:46:20,550 --> 00:46:23,950
What's going on?

556
00:46:24,110 --> 00:46:28,110
Excuse me...

557
00:46:31,980 --> 00:46:33,950
This is embarrassing.

558
00:46:34,110 --> 00:46:35,050
Let's go already.

559
00:46:35,210 --> 00:46:36,810
We should wait for Eun Bi!

560
00:46:36,950 --> 00:46:39,780
We just went through an embarassment all because of her.

561
00:46:39,950 --> 00:46:41,450
Let's just go.

562
00:46:41,580 --> 00:46:46,373
How come you become such a pain when
Hong Jae Yi isn't around?

563
00:46:46,580 --> 00:46:51,880
Forget it.
Let's just go to a cafe or something.

564
00:46:52,050 --> 00:46:57,580
Let's go to a cafe.
Text Eun Bi to come.

565
00:47:03,980 --> 00:47:06,750
Is it that you have guts?
Or that you have no shame?

566
00:47:06,910 --> 00:47:11,050
Or are you stupid?
Or are you really smart?

567
00:47:11,180 --> 00:47:18,780
And are you inferring that I'm ok no matter
what kinds of insults you throw at me?

568
00:47:18,950 --> 00:47:22,650
It's not that.

569
00:47:25,950 --> 00:47:33,510
When this book first came out,
I stood in line to buy this.

570
00:47:33,680 --> 00:47:36,550
I read it more than my textbook.

571
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:39,750
I read it with more attention.

572
00:47:39,880 --> 00:47:41,910
The reason I dreamed about musicals.

573
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:49,010
And the reason that kept me going was all
this book right here.

574
00:47:49,180 --> 00:47:53,280
When I saw you...
I wanted to get an autograph.

575
00:47:53,410 --> 00:47:58,380
I just wanted to make a good impression.

576
00:47:58,550 --> 00:48:13,350
Although it was quite heartbreaking today,
it's become really hard to see you again.

577
00:48:13,510 --> 00:48:16,010
But next time,

578
00:48:16,150 --> 00:48:20,310
I'll practice even harder and be here.

579
00:48:28,880 --> 00:48:32,710
That's really touching.

580
00:48:32,850 --> 00:48:37,850
I'll be cheering for you.

581
00:48:37,980 --> 00:48:45,435
Thank you!

582
00:48:50,010 --> 00:48:52,984
-Why did you?
-Let's start again.

583
00:48:52,984 --> 00:48:54,638
How many do we have left?

584
00:49:29,550 --> 00:49:34,180
So, by how much did she raise the key?

585
00:49:37,210 --> 00:49:43,200
What about Eun Bi?

586
00:49:46,950 --> 00:49:52,470
I see. I'll see you at the office.

587
00:50:05,750 --> 00:50:10,250
<i>The number you've dialed...</i>

588
00:50:10,410 --> 00:50:17,550
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

589
00:50:17,680 --> 00:50:21,550
Go Eun Bi.
You're not someone who can't sing.

590
00:50:21,680 --> 00:50:25,850
You're definitely not someone not qualified
for doing musicals.

591
00:50:25,980 --> 00:50:29,750
And also.

592
00:50:29,880 --> 00:50:32,352
About how you stood until the end.

593
00:50:32,352 --> 00:50:35,078
Thank you!

594
00:51:07,850 --> 00:51:11,780
Are you alright?

595
00:51:12,480 --> 00:51:15,910
I am alright, thank you.

596
00:51:16,050 --> 00:51:19,610
Did something happen during the competition?

597
00:51:19,750 --> 00:51:22,550
No.

598
00:51:22,710 --> 00:51:28,580
I sang really happily.

599
00:51:28,750 --> 00:51:32,771
In front of the person that I respect the most.

600
00:51:32,771 --> 00:51:37,150
I sang the song I really liked.

601
00:51:37,310 --> 00:51:44,810
Thank you!

602
00:52:01,150 --> 00:52:03,010
Are you going to watch the whole thing?

603
00:52:03,150 --> 00:52:07,310
I didn't edit. It's really long.

604
00:52:08,850 --> 00:52:13,350
No. I just need to watch one of them.
It should be the 7th.

605
00:52:13,480 --> 00:52:17,910
The title is... "Chung Dam Dong's Nine Tails. "

606
00:52:18,050 --> 00:52:20,880
It's the one they did when I was out.

607
00:52:21,010 --> 00:52:23,980
Kang Hee had a strange reaction to it.

608
00:52:23,980 --> 00:52:26,950
-Who says that?
-Director Cha who shot the film.

609
00:52:27,080 --> 00:52:34,180
Although Kang Hee isn't the nicest person,
he said that she was especially hard on them.

610
00:52:35,650 --> 00:52:38,710
What did you make with for this?

611
00:52:38,850 --> 00:52:41,550
Something there.

612
00:52:41,680 --> 00:52:44,380
You should have just asked me to do it.

613
00:52:44,550 --> 00:52:48,250
You said that guys who can't cook
are not even guys.

614
00:52:48,380 --> 00:52:51,480
Who says that?

615
00:53:00,850 --> 00:53:05,150
-Her!
-Shh!

616
00:53:22,450 --> 00:53:27,350
<i>A piece like this,
can be put on a big stage on a bigger scale.</i>

617
00:53:27,510 --> 00:53:31,150
You don't want to sponsor them, but
make a full production investment?

618
00:53:31,280 --> 00:53:34,537
That's right.
The content is interesting.

619
00:53:34,537 --> 00:53:36,371
Music is even better.

620
00:53:36,371 --> 00:53:40,613
And in my opinion, this "Chung Dam Dong Nine Tails"
has a very good Asian taste to it.

621
00:53:40,613 --> 00:53:42,768
It can be even be exported worldwide.

622
00:53:43,050 --> 00:53:48,580
Let's make a piece that will earn us the money.

623
00:53:48,750 --> 00:53:52,650
If it can happen.
What could I possibly ask for?

624
00:53:52,810 --> 00:53:56,282
But...
The reason they hid the writer --

625
00:53:56,282 --> 00:53:59,316
We should check if there are problems.

626
00:53:59,316 --> 00:54:03,080
We will have to see if it's original.

627
00:54:03,250 --> 00:54:05,951
There are no other problems except you.

628
00:54:05,951 --> 00:54:07,350
What?

629
00:54:07,480 --> 00:54:11,461
Us buying the song and producing it.
There are no problems.

630
00:54:11,461 --> 00:54:24,080
I'm just not sure if you will continue liking the piece,
after you've found out who wrote the songs.

631
00:55:21,450 --> 00:55:27,005
Who's the writer that's impressed you so much?

632
00:55:37,450 --> 00:55:40,880
Is this Representative Gu Jak?
This is Yu Jin from Amour Fund.

633
00:55:41,050 --> 00:55:44,580
Yes I saw you at the competition.

634
00:55:44,710 --> 00:55:50,889
Don't worry about me.
What she said was all true.

635
00:55:51,568 --> 00:55:55,219
It is wrong.
I didn't write the song just for anyone.

636
00:55:55,219 --> 00:55:57,995
I won't edit it to suit others' voices either.

637
00:55:58,550 --> 00:56:00,191
It's not like that.

638
00:56:00,191 --> 00:56:04,061
It's a good piece.
Make it suitable for a lot of people.

639
00:56:04,061 --> 00:56:06,616
Lots of people watching it. Isn't that great?

640
00:56:06,616 --> 00:56:09,140
This is a song that suited Go Eun Bi!

641
00:56:09,140 --> 00:56:11,365
Geez!

642
00:56:12,910 --> 00:56:16,161
Anyway the objective was,
to get this piece sponsored.

643
00:56:16,161 --> 00:56:18,280
As long as we accomplish that.

644
00:56:18,410 --> 00:56:22,161
And as long as I get better like it's been scheduled.

645
00:56:22,161 --> 00:56:24,462
Doha in "Chung Dang Dong Nine Tails."

646
00:56:24,462 --> 00:56:26,324
What?

647
00:56:27,610 --> 00:56:31,950
It's me. Is it out already?

648
00:56:34,280 --> 00:56:37,510
What?

649
00:56:38,980 --> 00:56:42,010
He wants to go big scale from the start.

650
00:56:42,180 --> 00:56:42,710
You know?

651
00:56:42,850 --> 00:56:46,910
The Jin Dynasty background.
And the Roman Empire background.

652
00:56:47,050 --> 00:56:52,310
What lines do we need? We just need to put
it up on the stage!

653
00:56:52,480 --> 00:56:55,380
They don't want to sponsor it. But
they want to produce it themselves?

654
00:56:55,510 --> 00:56:58,050
Yes! Co-producing.

655
00:56:58,210 --> 00:57:00,810
-Forget it.
-Jae Yi.

656
00:57:00,980 --> 00:57:06,400
I'm really sorry to break your dreams.
You know Yu Jin?

657
00:57:06,400 --> 00:57:08,319
If he finds out that I'm the one who wrote the song -

658
00:57:08,319 --> 00:57:09,750
He does.

659
00:57:09,880 --> 00:57:12,350
He already knew.

660
00:57:12,480 --> 00:57:16,310
So his condition was that you write all of the songs.

661
00:57:16,450 --> 00:57:17,580
Jae Yi.

662
00:57:17,710 --> 00:57:22,510
To me this is like,
jackpot in a lottery.

663
00:57:22,680 --> 00:57:25,250
It's like getting the apartment.

664
00:57:25,410 --> 00:57:29,007
It's like Jeon Ji Hyun falling for me on a blind date.
And her wanting to be in my shows.

665
00:57:29,007 --> 00:57:34,410
It's like all of these happening at once.

666
00:57:34,550 --> 00:57:39,150
They want to put in 4 million for my music.

667
00:58:23,880 --> 00:58:29,010
<i>~I will say all of the things honestly today.~</i>

668
00:58:29,150 --> 00:58:33,980
<i>~My last...~</i>

669
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:41,880
<i>~My last...~</i>

670
00:58:44,980 --> 00:58:49,880
<i>~My last breath will tell it.~</i>

671
00:58:50,010 --> 00:59:12,310
<i>~He is my only love.~</i>

672
00:59:56,050 --> 00:59:57,810
That's good.

673
00:59:57,980 --> 01:00:02,480
This song is yours.

674
01:00:03,680 --> 01:00:07,450
Should I make it so that only you can sing it?

675
01:00:07,580 --> 01:00:10,880
You have no idea how good the kids are
at singing.

676
01:00:11,050 --> 01:00:13,310
No...

677
01:00:13,450 --> 01:00:17,050
I'll make it recognizable by everyone.

678
01:00:17,180 --> 01:00:25,310
This song is written by Hong Jae Yi for Bae Kang Hee.

679
01:00:25,480 --> 01:00:30,410
Others won't be able to sing it.

680
01:01:04,610 --> 01:01:05,971
Yes.

681
01:01:15,850 --> 01:01:17,880
What is this?

682
01:01:18,010 --> 01:01:19,150
This?

683
01:01:19,633 --> 01:01:21,072
What do you mean by 'this'?

684
01:01:26,772 --> 01:01:37,772
Subtitles by DramaFever

